Stevens Mokgalapa has been voted out as Tshwane Mayor. 111 council members voted in favour of the motion of no confidence. Courtesy #Dstv403 PRETORIA – Stevens Mokgalapa has been voted out as Tshwane mayor. 111 council members voted in favour of the motion of no confidence against Mokgalapa. READ: Bobani booted as Nelson Mandela Bay mayor Speaker Katlego Mathebe was also voted out earlier. Chaos erupted in the council over the election of an acting speaker. The ANC says it's on a mission to reclaim the metro after it won back Johannesburg on Wednesday but the DA says this is a coup.